he city's transition from Federalist to Whig politics. He had previously served one term in the US House of Representatives (1817-1819) as a Federalist, and was a delegate to the 1818 Connecticut Constitutional Convention."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"President of Hartford Fire Insurance for 25 years","body":"He served as president of the Hartford Fire Insurance Company from 1810 to 1835 — a 25-year tenure spanning the company's early growth into one of New England's leading insurers. He simultaneously served as president of the Hartford Bank from 1819 to 1828."}],"former_ids":[],"career":[],"is_placeholder":false,"slug":"nathaniel-terry-1768"},"HD1331":{"id":"HD1331","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":6,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":true,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"generation_from_john_talcott":5,"hooker_talcott_convergence":true},"parents":{"father_id":"T00387","mother_id":"H00362"},"tags":["hooker_talcott_descent"],"sources":[{"entry":"863","label":"Edward Hooker 1909"}],"birth":{"year":1774,"month":1,"day":17,"city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut"},"death":{"year":1841,"month":10,"day":26,"city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"X00421","children_ids":["HD1345","HD1346","HD1347","HD1348","HD1349","HD1350","HD1351","HD1352"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1798,"date_month":3,"date_day":14,"location_city":"Hartford","location_state":"Connecticut"}],"gender":"female","artworks":["ART006"],"number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"header":"Mother of an author and a Union general","body":"Catherine Wadsworth married Nathaniel Terry, one of Hartford's most prominent citizens, in 1798. The Hooker-Talcott blood that ran through her passed to her grandchildren: Rose Terry Cooke became one of New England's most cel